Rating: 3
For those who are looking for a "variation" on traditional canned enchilada sauce -- try looking for Mole ("MOL-ay") (I prefer Green) or Pipian (pumpkin seeds) in the hispanic food section. I found it in my standard supermarket, but you may have to try the tiny bodega on the corner. The jar you purchase is 4:1 concentrate that you mix with water or broth. Dont make the whole jar at once, and it takes some stirring to get it to combine, but once you do, its fantastic. Try it as a replacement!!

